Product Description:

An interactive virtual map, available in both Street View format and 2D layout, of the UADY Faculty of Mathematics. It’s designed to help new students, applicants, and visitors easily find and learn about different areas of the faculty, providing useful information about each location and improving the overall user experience.

Scope:

Our project has two main components:

A visual representation of the Faculty of Mathematics in both 2D schematic view and a virtual Street View-style environment.

The ability for users to click on different areas within the map to see relevant information—such as opening and closing hours, the staff in charge of each area, and any notes about ongoing or upcoming events.

Limitations:

There are some limitations to our project. The biggest one is keeping the information up to date, since most of it will need to be updated manually by administrators (except for more permanent data like general hours of operation and class schedules).
Other limitations include the limited fluidity of the Street View experience—it will only support fixed-point transitions rather than continuous movement. Additionally, because this system is meant to provide updated information, an internet connection will be required. The map will only cover the Faculty of Mathematics facilities.

Users / Customers:

While the main audience is university applicants, any current student or member of the public interested in the faculty’s layout and information can use the map.

Primary users: University applicants

Secondary users: New students and current students

Potential users: Visitors from outside the faculty, such as people from other campuses, food delivery drivers, company/institution representatives, and guest speakers.

Value Proposition:

Right now, there is no way to remotely explore the Faculty of Mathematics online using real and up-to-date images in a Street View perspective. What makes our product different is its virtual interactivity and ease of remote access. It meets the need to learn about the Faculty of Mathematics and quickly get useful information about the facilities—without having to be there in person.
